  "observation": "The scorer compares appFitness against the previous run's appFitness. For deterministic agents (same code, same tests), this always yields 0 improvement after the first run. Evolution only measures delta, not absolute performance.",
  "suggestion": "Seed v2 should include both absolute fitness (how well the agent performs) and relative fitness (how much it improved). EQS should weight both: stable high performance is valuable, not just improvement spikes.",
